5. Meaning objects as structured records

Each concept on the map should have a record.

Example:

MeaningObject {
  id
  label
  aliases
  definition
  mythic_projection
  linguistic_projection
  structural_projection
  domains
  invariants
  related_objects
  field_memberships
  certainty
  source_lineage
}

Example object:

label: Delayed Feedback
aliases: hidden return, deferred consequence
definition: actions whose effects arrive after a time lag
mythic_projection: Green Knight / return blow
linguistic_projection: delayed consequence chain
structural_projection: state(t) -> effect(t+Δ)
domains: economics, ecology, psychology, control systems
invariants: latency, accumulation, return

That one record can power the whole map.

