10. Color and music encoding

Your earlier insight fits here naturally.

The Atlas can use color and sound as compact overlays.

Color

A concept’s color can encode:
	•	relation family
	•	certainty
	•	valence
	•	domain blend

For example:
	•	green = growth / increase
	•	blue = structure / stability
	•	red = causation / force / danger
	•	gold = invariant / high confidence
	•	violet = cross-domain bridge

Not fixed forever, but systematic.

Music

A concept’s chord or interval profile can encode:
	•	harmony with nearby ideas
	•	tension
	•	contradiction
	•	transformation arc

A stable theory cluster might sound consonant.
A contradiction zone might sound dissonant.

This makes the Atlas multi-sensory and compressive.

