17. How it would work with the Semantic Loom

The Loom and Atlas are complementary.

Loom

Turns language into stitching and back.

Atlas

Displays and navigates the stitched world.

Pipeline:

Embroidery
→ Loom extraction
→ Meaning tensor graph
→ Atlas projection
→ user explores / reasons / edits
→ Loom re-renders to embroidery

So the Loom is the translator.
The Atlas is the terrain.

