18. Why this matters

Linear text is powerful but limited.

A map does several things text cannot do well:
	•	show simultaneity
	•	show neighborhoods
	•	show tension
	•	show missing bridges
	•	show possible routes
	•	show hidden structure

A true Atlas of Meaning Space would make reasoning feel less like scrolling and more like navigating a world.

That would be a real interface breakthrough.

